Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie drew two examples (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.73, 31 and 181, 26). Name Timodikos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0221.41.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0995)
